text: Nashua is a city in southern New Hampshire, United States. As of the 2020 census, Nashua had a population of 91,322. It is the second-largest city in the state and in northern New England after nearby Manchester. Nashua is, along with Manchester, one of two seats of New Hampshire's most populous county, Hillsborough County. ==References== Category:Cities in New Hampshire Category:County seats in New Hampshire
title: Nashua, New Hampshire
